Second Brother
The second brother is one of the narrator's older siblings who died of illness.<SEP>The second brother is the other twin older sibling who sleeps on the narrator's right side and dies of a serious illness.

Narrator
The narrator is a person who has two older brothers and admits to killing the eldest brother after the second brother died of illness.<SEP>The narrator is a younger sibling of twin brothers and shares a bed with them, later experiencing discomfort after one brother's death.

Illness
Illness is the cause of death for the second brother.

Bed
The bed is where the three brothers have slept together since they were young.

Eldest Brother
The eldest brother is the oldest of the three siblings and was killed by the narrator.<SEP>The eldest brother is one of the twin older siblings who sleeps on the narrator's left side.

Serious Illness
A serious illness is the cause of the second brother's death.

Puzzle Answer
The puzzle answer is a narrative riddle describing a disturbing yet logically structured scenario involving siblings and a bed.

Shared Bed
The shared bed is where the narrator and their two older brothers have slept together since childhood.
